  "title": "[release-1.25] Bump konnectivity-client to 0.0.37",
  "body": "#### What type of PR is this?\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n#### What this PR does / why we need it:\r\n\r\nFixes memory leaks (affecting proxy-server and proxy-agent).\r\n\r\n#### Which issue(s) this PR fixes:\r\n\r\nThe desired fix: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/apiserver-network-proxy/pull/467\r\n\r\n#### Special notes for your reviewer:\r\n\r\nMaster branch took this fix in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/116348, but here we use the more backport friendly tag [0.0.37](https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/apiserver-network-proxy/releases/tag/konnectivity-client%2Fv0.0.37) rather than [0.1.2](https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/apiserver-network-proxy/releases/tag/konnectivity-client%2Fv0.1.2).\r\n\r\nDiff from 0.0.36 to 0.0.37: [github compare](https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/apiserver-network-proxy/compare/konnectivity-client/v0.0.36...konnectivity-client/v0.0.37)\r\n\r\n#### Does this PR introduce a user-facing change?\r\n```release-note\r\nNONE\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Additional documentation e.g., KEPs (Kubernetes Enhancement Proposals), usage docs, etc.:\r\n\r\n```docs\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
